  "1.25 and 0.75": "",
  "For this symmetric matrix, the singular values equal the absolute values of the eigenvalues. Eigenvalues: (1-lambda)^2 - 0.25 = 0, so 1-lambda = +/-0.5, giving lambda = 0.5 and 1.5. Both are positive, so the singular values are 1.5 and 0.5.": "",
  "A chemical engineer models a reaction network with 3 species. The rate matrix is A = [[-2, 1, 0],[1, -2, 1],[0, 1, -2]]. What property of A guarantees conservation of total concentration?": "",
  "The matrix is symmetric": "",
  "Each column sums to zero, so total concentration is constant": "",
  "All eigenvalues are negative": "",
  "The determinant is zero": "",
  "Each column of A sums to 0 (e.g., -2+1+0=0), meaning d(total)/dt = sum of all dx_i/dt = (1,1,1) * A * x = 0 for all x. This conservation law ensures that species are transformed but not created or destroyed.": "",
  "A robotics engineer has a 2-link planar robot arm. The Jacobian matrix J relates joint velocities to end-effector velocity. If J = [[2, 1],[0, 3]] and joint velocities are (1, 2) rad/s, what is the end-effector velocity?": "",
