  "v = J * q_dot = [[2,1],[0,3]] * (1,2) = (2*1+1*2, 0*1+3*2) = (4, 6). The Jacobian linearly maps joint velocities to the end-effector's Cartesian velocity.": "",
  "A power systems engineer models a 3-bus network. The admittance matrix Y has the property that each row sums to zero (for an isolated network). If Y = [[3,-1,-2],[-1,2,-1],[-2,-1,3]], what does the null space of Y represent?": "",
