  "Reactive power at each bus following conventional understanding": "",
  "Since rows sum to zero, Y*(1,1,1)^T = 0, meaning the vector (1,1,1) is in the null space. This means adding the same voltage to all buses produces zero current flow -- only voltage differences drive current.": "",
  "An aerospace engineer uses the matrix exponential e^(At) to solve x' = Ax for a satellite attitude control system where A = [[0, 1],[-4, 0]]. The eigenvalues of A are +/-2i. What type of behavior does the satellite exhibit?": "",
  "Exponential decay to equilibrium": "",
  "Pure oscillation (undamped) because eigenvalues are purely imaginary": "",
  "Chaotic behavior": "",
  "Exponential growth because eigenvalues are nonzero": "",
  "Purely imaginary eigenvalues (+/-2i) produce sinusoidal oscillations with frequency 2 rad/s and no growth or decay. The satellite oscillates perpetually about its equilibrium, neither stabilizing nor diverging.": "",
  "A telecommunications engineer designs a network routing system where traffic at 3 nodes is redistributed each hour by matrix P = [[0.5, 0.3, 0.2],[0.3, 0.4, 0.3],[0.2, 0.3, 0.5]]. Starting with traffic vector t = (100, 200, 300), what is the total traffic after one redistribution step?": "",
  "300, particularl": "",
  "700, particularl": "",
  "600 (same as before)": "",
  "500, particularl": "",
  "Each column of P sums to 1 (it is column-stochastic), so total traffic is conserved: sum(P*t) = (1,1,1)*P*t = (1,1,1)*t = 100+200+300 = 600. Redistribution moves traffic between nodes without creating or destroying it.": ""
